author: Justin Harp
title: TV show ratings: Empire halts its descent as Supernatural dips on Wednesday - Arrow Cult -
text: Empire halted its three-week ratings descent on Wednesday (October 21), according to Nielsen figures.The Fox drama series climbed two-tenths of a point to 4.8 (12.28m) at 9pm, after Rosewood rose two-tenths with 1.6 (5.27m) at 8pm. © Fox / Chuck Hodes Fox dominated the key 18-49 demographic on Wednesday with 3.2.ABC's The Middle took 1.9 (7.08m) at 8pm, The Goldbergs hit 2.1 (6.48m) at 8.30pm, Modern Family improved a tenth with 2.7 (7.80m) at 9pm, and Black-ish averaged 1.8 (5.79m) at 9.30pm.At 10pm on ABC, Nashville fell to 1.1 (4.47m). © The CW / Diyah Pera Arrow matched last week's score of 0.9 (2.40m) at 8pm on The CW, while Supernatural slid two-tenths to 0.6 (1.59m) at 9pm.Survivor held steady with 2.1 (9.10m) at 8pm on CBS. Later in the night, Criminal Minds and Code Black picked up 1.6 (8.47m) at 9pm and 1.2 (7.13m) at 10pm.NBC's The Mysteries of Laura interested 1.1 (6.81m) at 8pm, Law & Order: SVU received 1.5 (6.33m) at 9pm and Chicago PD dropped a tenth to 1.4 (6.24m) at 10pm.
